sourceQuestion:
Let f: R -> R be a function such that f(x) = max(x, x^3), x in R, where R is the set of all real numbers. The set of all points where f(x) is NOT differentiable is

A. {-1, 1, 2}
B. {-1, 0, 1}
C. {0, 1}
D. {-1, 0, 1, 2}

If f(x_n) * f(x_{n+1}) < 0 then

A. There must be a root of f(x) between x_n and x_{n+1}
B. There need not be a root of f(x) between x_n and x_{n+1}
C. There is a fourth derivative of f(x) with respect to x that vanishes at x_1
D. The fourth derivative of f(x) with respect to x vanishes at x_{n+1}
